# AGENTS.md

This file defines practical guidance for AI coding assistants in this workspace.

## AI assistants (Cursor / MCP)

1. Enable the **`ronyup` MCP server** (`.cursor/mcp.json` or `.ai/mcp/mcp.json`).
2. **Start every RonyKit task** by reading `.agents/skills/ronykit-framework/SKILL.md` (invoke `/ronykit-framework` when your client supports skills).
3. Read architecture and package guidance from **MCP knowledge resources** ÔÇö do not invent service layout. Index:
   `.agents/skills/ronykit-framework/references/mcp-map.md`.
{{ if .Skills }}
## Skill routing (read SKILL.md ÔÇö do not rely on memory)

Specialized skills live under `.agents/skills/`. For each applicable row, **open and read** the skill file before coding ÔÇö this is required even for small models that skip optional pointers.

| Task | Read these skills (in order) |
|------|------------------------------|
| New backend feature | `ronykit-framework` Ôćĺ MCP `design-new-service` |
| Repo / persistence | `go-testing` + MCP `architecture/integration-tests` |
| Bootstrap frontend | `frontend-design`, `design-tokens`, `typography` + MCP `design-frontend` |
| Dashboard / admin UI | `dashboard-ui`, `shadcn`, `ux-quality` |
| Agent-friendly UI / WebMCP | `webmcp`, `nextjs-modern`, `ux-quality` |
| Next.js routes / data | `nextjs-modern`, `shadcn` |
| UI components | `shadcn`, `storybook`, `ux-quality` |
| Frontend tests | `frontend-testing`, `verification-before-completion` |
| Go style / tests | `go-modern`, `go-testing`, `writing-tests` |
| Before claiming done | `verification-before-completion`, `code-formatting` |

